body: Looks good to me, this should probably be merged quickly, so that people can build again.
Previous Test Aborted. New Check Test Started: https://jenkins.esgyn.com/job/Check-PR-master/607/

The customers are expected to install hadoop using the chosen distro processes. They can choose any specific version of 1.1.2 because Trafodion is expected to work with any version starting with 1.1.2. Install_local_hadoop is meant for contributing organization like Esgyn or contributors. This is supposed to point to the local repository. In the local repository we can always soft link a more specific version to the major version like 1.1.2.
Looks good. I suppose TEST106 is being disabled for some other reason? Merging...
TEST106 was disabled because of hang issue in drop statement. Prashanth will create a JIRA and work on it.

The right thing to do is not hard code the tar file name instead create a softlink to tarfile wherever the tar file is stored on the system. So no additional change is required.

This additional change can be abandoned.
Can you please update the PR heading and the comments so that it is easy for the reviewers to understand what is being done in this PR
A new JIRA indicating what got missed with the earlier commit for TRAFODION-1706 would be better too.
Looks like this is ready to commit.
If the last column is a NULL, this change will add a space. Need to fix it again...

I changed the implementation: not replace the \r with \n, but return back the previous pointer before \r inside the hdfs_strchr() function. And in the caller, add that extra position when it needs to move to next field.
Test with INT/DATE/String, all works well, also test with last column as null, works fine too.

Change looks good to me. Can you please modify the new test to insert into trafodion table with date as a last column. Also add another test for numeric column as the last column and insert into trafodion table too.
Sounds good, if that helps. Is this a temporary change or should we permanently move to the new repo?
The https://repo1.maven.org/maven2 is the commonly used central maven repository. So I would recommend this be the permanent repo.

Anoop, your commits almost always come from centos user.  That stays in the code history forever. It would be helpful that you could set your git user info when you set up new VM, before making commits. Thanks.
Thanks Selva, I will add the test for numeric/date data

Previous Test Aborted. New Check Test Started: https://jenkins.esgyn.com/job/Check-PR-master/626/

BTW, I ran the full regression test with forcing the new CQD to 2.0 in sbdefs file and verified all the FAILS where understood and normal due to new line showing up on explain. The regular regression still does not have this cqd set as this is not maint to be one by default but only activated on a case by case basis, since there is no compiler support for this feature yet.

I am seeing that we instantiate HTable which is marked as @InterfaceAudience.Private.

Also, the note in the class says that "HTable is no longer a client API. Use Table instead. It is marked InterfaceAudience.Private indicating that this is an HBase-internal class as defined in Hadoop Interface Classification There are no guarantees for backwards source / binary compatibility and methods or class can change or go away without deprecation".

Are we ok with it?

well, we have been OK so far to use non public API. Yes it causes trouble, it is one more. Unfortunately.
Given that this feature is off by default, worse case, we don't enable it...
